# Study Notebook — Product Thinking Document
**AI-Focused Product Design**
Version 1.0 | Personal Portfolio Project

---

## 1. The Context Behind This Product

This tool was built by me, for me.

I am actively searching for a PM or TPM role in tech. The job market is competitive. Getting an offer requires doing several things consistently and well at the same time: practicing case interviews, applying to enough companies every day, and maintaining outreach to recruiters and hiring managers. Each of these activities compounds over time. Missing a day on any of them sets you back more than it seems.

The four tabs in this product map directly to what a serious job seeker has to do to compete:

**Product Case** and **TPM Case** cover the interview skill gap. PM and TPM interviews have a specific format, and performance in them is a learnable skill. It requires repeated deliberate practice with feedback, not passive reading.

**Habits** covers the job search volume problem. Five job applications and two recruiter outreach messages per day is the minimum consistent effort needed to generate enough pipeline. Most people track this loosely or not at all. Streaks make the consistency visible and meaningful.

**Progress** closes the loop. Without a way to see whether your interview scores are actually improving over time, practice feels arbitrary. The progress view turns sessions into a measurable trajectory.

Each tab solves a distinct part of the same problem: landing the job.

