## 2. Problem Statement

### The User

A career-transitioning professional preparing for PM and TPM interviews at tech companies. Self-directed, motivated, but without access to structured coaching or peer mock interview partners on demand.

### The Job To Be Done

"Help me practice interviewing in a way that actually makes me better, not just more familiar with frameworks."

### What Existing Solutions Get Wrong

| Tool | What it offers | What it misses |
|---|---|---|
| Exponent / IGotAnOffer | Video walkthroughs, sample answers | Passive consumption with no practice loop |
| ChatGPT (unstructured) | On-demand feedback | No memory, no progression, no accountability |
| Peer mock interviews | Real conversation feel | Hard to schedule, inconsistent quality |
| Notion habit trackers | Habit logging | No intelligence, just a checkbox |

### The Gap

No tool combines a structured 8-step interview framework, an AI that behaves like a real interviewer rather than a tutor, adaptive difficulty based on past performance, and daily habit tracking in one place designed for studying.

